:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:187.8pt"><p style="margin:4pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Out of date assumption on income elasticity of demand</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#1f497d; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.75pt; border-left-color:#1f497d; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.75pt; border-top-color:#1f497d; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.75pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:187.75pt"><p style="margin:4pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Yes, updated</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#1f497d; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.75pt; border-right-color:#1f497d; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.75pt; border-top-color:#1f497d; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.75pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:187.8pt"><p style="margin:4pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Use of over-long appraisal period </span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#1f497d; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.75pt; border-left-color:#1f497d; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.75pt; border-top-color:#1f497d; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.75pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:187.75pt"><p style="margin:4pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Judgment call. The appraisal period used is consistent with HM Treasury Green Book guidance but with demand growth cut off three years after project opening. How can this be over-long?</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#1f497d; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.75pt; border-right-color:#1f497d; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.75pt; border-top-color:#1f497d; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.75pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:187.8pt"><p style="margin:4pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Over-statement of crowding benefits</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#1f497d; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.75pt; border-left-color:#1f497d; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.75pt; border-top-color:#1f497d; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.75pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:187.75pt"><p style="margin:4pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Yes, t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">rain lengthening investments included in revised base case</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#1f497d; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.75pt; border-right-color:#1f497d; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.75pt; border-top-color:#1f497d; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.75pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:187.8pt"><p style="margin:4pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Doubts over validity of reliability benefits</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#1f497d; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.75pt; border-left-color:#1f497d; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.75pt; border-top-color:#1f497d; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.75pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:187.75pt"><p style="margin:4pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Yes. A lot of new evidence provided on the extent of train punctuality and its relationship with the intensity of network use</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#1f497d; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.75pt; border-right-color:#1f497d; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.75pt; border-to